---
description: "Force broad subagent participation with required outputs, N/A policy, and no stale artifacts"
alwaysApply: true
---

General:
- Artifact root (ARTIFACTS_DIR, default artifacts/current) is ephemeral and must be reset at the start of /feature and /epicify runs. With --epic-id=<N>.<k>: ARTIFACTS_DIR=artifacts/epic-<N>.<k>.
- Required agents must produce their artifact for the CURRENT run-id, not rely on old files.
- Empty files are forbidden. If an agent is not applicable, it must write an explicit N/A section with reason.

Planning runs (/feature, /epicify):
Required planning agents and outputs (written under artifact root):
- business-analyst -> discovery.md
- ux-designer -> ux.md
- principal-architect -> architecture.md (N/A allowed if no architecture changes)
- solution-designer -> solution.md (N/A allowed if no ops/config changes)
- qa-strategist -> qa.md
- security-privacy -> security-design.md

Feature-conditional planning agents and outputs:
- art-director -> art-direction.md (required for UI/look-and-feel/visual epics; otherwise N/A)
- game-designer -> game-feel.md (required for gameplay/minigame/difficulty epics; otherwise N/A)
- motion-audio-designer -> motion-audio.md (required for animation/audio epics; otherwise N/A)
- illustrator -> assets.md (required when the feature requests visuals/assets/minigames; otherwise N/A)

N/A policy:
- If a discipline does not apply, the artifact MUST include:
  - "N/A: <reason>"
  - "Impact: none"
  - "Checks still required: <yes/no + short list>"

Run manifest (hard requirement):
- The orchestrator must maintain {artifact root}/run-manifest.md that includes:
  - run id
  - required agents list
  - for each agent: status OK or N/A with reason + artifact path
- If manifest or any required artifact is missing: BLOCKED.

Delivery runs (/orchestrate-task):
Always dispatch:
- implementer-web, tester, reviewer
Always validate (near end):
- security, performance
Conditionally dispatch:
- implementer-api if any A-lanes are touched
- deps-infra if any I-lanes are touched
- db if any D-lanes are touched

Playwright policy:
- Playwright (including screenshot tests) must run only via docker compose e2e service.

Merge readiness:
- MERGE-READY is forbidden unless CI is green and required artifacts (including run manifest) exist for the current run.